  "title": "feat(react-instantsearch): provide codemods to help with migration",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for submitting a pull request!\r\n  Please provide enough information so that others can review your pull request.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Summary**\r\n\r\n### [FX-2390](https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/FX-2390)\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\nRefer to the [README](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/blob/feat/react-instantsearch-codemods/packages/react-instantsearch-hooks/scripts/transforms/README.md) to see what each script does.\r\n\r\nInstead of publishing it as a package, we could simply mention in the docs that the scripts can be downloaded with `curl` or `wget` so that it can be reviewed and changed, `addWidget-to-addWidgets` was not published either.\r\n\r\nFew limitations are : \r\n\r\n- `defaultRefinement` can't really be handled as the script is ran file by file, so I decided to just add a TODO comment\r\n- If a `translations` object or `showMore`, `page` or `ariaPage` are not defined inline, it's not easy to modify so we just add a TODO comment as well\r\n- Code is a little hard to read, I could perhaps look into migrating to TypeScript if it's worth it\r\n\r\n\r\n[FX-2390]: https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/FX-2390?atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiNWRkNTljNzYxNjVmNDY3MDlhMDU5Y2ZhYzA5YTRkZjUiLCJwIjoiZ2l0aHViLWNvbS1KU1cifQ",
